    "## OBJECTIVE\nFix bugs and improve MermaidXP (mxp.apulab.com), a Mermaid diagram viewer/editor deployed via Cloudflare Workers. Current focus: fixing a bug where zoom doesn't work when in markdown sheets mode (loading a .md file with multiple mermaid diagrams).\n\n## USER GUIDANCE\n- Write minimal code — no verbose implementations\n- Deploy to `mxp.apulab.com` via Cloudflare Workers after fixes\n- User communicates primarily in Spanish\n- Stop guessing — use sequential thinking to understand root causes\n- The user explicitly tests in a real browser (not Playwright), as Playwright synthetic events don't always reproduce real bugs\n\n## COMPLETED\n\n### Previous Sessions (33 issues created and closed)\nSecurity fixes, performance optimization (bundle 766KB→355KB), type safety (51 `any` types replaced), console cleanup (44→0), toolbar UX improvements, Apache 2.0 LICENSE, ARCHITECTURE.md, export logic extraction, etc.\n\n### Current Session — Four Bugs Fixed\n\n1. **Icon disappearance during drag (#57)** — Root cause: `selectElement()` in `canvasElementsSlice.ts` did `push` without clearing previous selection, so clicking icon B after A resulted in `['A', 'B']`. Then `moveSelectedElements` applied total delta as incremental (`position += totalDelta`), causing exponential drift. Fix: clear selection on click (unless Shift held) + track `lastPosition` for incremental deltas in multi-select drag. Files: `CanvasElementInteractions.tsx`, `canvasElementsSlice.ts`.\n\n2. **Click-to-place blocked in pan mode** — `onMouseDownCapture` in `DiagramDisplay.tsx` did `stopPropagation()` on all SVG clicks in pan mode, preventing `onClick` from firing. Fix: skip pan intercept when `placingElement` is active.\n\n3. **Pan interfering with element placement** — `onMouseDown` handler initiated pan operations during placement mode. Fix: `onMouseDown={placingElement ? undefined : handleMouseDown}` in `DiagramDisplay.tsx`.\n\n4. **Click-to-place text invisible (wrong coordinates)** — Manual formula `(x - pan.x) / zoom` produced wrong SVG coordinates because React state values didn't match actual CSS transform matrix. Fix: use `getScreenCTM().inverse()` on the `custom-elements-layer` for accurate screen→SVG coordinate conversion in `useElementPlacement.ts`.\n\n### Bug Currently Under Investigation\n**Zoom doesn't work in markdown sheets mode** — When user loads a `.md` file containing mermaid diagrams, the app enters \"sheets mode\" (`SheetsView` component) which renders diagrams differently from `DiagramDisplay`. The zoom controls in the toolbar don't affect `SheetsView` because it has its own renderer (`SheetRenderer`) that doesn't use the canvas zoom/pan state.\n\n## TECHNICAL CONTEXT\n\n### Two Rendering Paths\n- `MainCanvas.tsx` line 19: `{sheetsCount > 0 ? <SheetsView /> : <DiagramDisplay />}`\n- `DiagramDisplay` has full zoom/pan/placement support via Redux `canvas` slice\n- `SheetsView` uses its own `SheetRenderer` component with no zoom/pan integration\n\n### Key Files for Sheets/Zoom Bug\n- `src/components/canvas/MainCanvas.tsx` — switches between SheetsView and DiagramDisplay based on `state.diagram.sheets.length`\n- `src/components/canvas/SheetsView.tsx` — renders sheets with prev/next navigation, uses `SheetRenderer`\n- `src/components/canvas/DiagramDisplay.tsx` — full-featured canvas with zoom/pan\n- `src/components/canvas/ToolbarImproved.tsx` — zoom buttons dispatch `zoomIn()`/`zoomOut()`/`resetZoom()` to Redux `canvas` slice\n- `src/store/slices/canvasSlice.ts` — holds `zoom`, `pan`, `interactionMode`, `placingElement`\n- `src/components/header/FileOperations.tsx` — handles `.md` file loading, calls `dispatch(setSheets(sheets))` for multi-diagram markdown files\n\n### SVG Structure (DiagramDisplay mode)\n```\n<svg style=\"transform: translate(panX, panY) scale(zoom)\">\n  <g data-diagram-content=\"true\">\n    <g data-custom-elements-layer class=\"custom-elements-layer\">\n```\n\n### Two Custom Element Systems (architectural debt)\n1. **`useElementPlacement.ts`** — Places elements directly into SVG DOM, NO Redux store\n2. **`CanvasElementRenderer.tsx`** — Syncs Redux `canvasElements` store to DOM\n\n### Coordinate Conversion Pattern (established fix)\nUse `getScreenCTM().inverse()` on the target SVG group for accurate screen→SVG coordinate conversion, instead of manual `(x - pan.x) / zoom` formula.\n\n## TOOLS EXECUTED\n- Multiple `npm run build && git push && npx wrangler deploy` cycles\n- Playwright MCP used to test placement and verify DOM state (but can't reproduce real user interaction bugs)\n- MutationObserver injected via Playwright to verify text elements are added but not removed\n- `grep` extensively used to trace code paths across the codebase\n- Git commits: `a4fe1f1` (icon fix), `d548d51` (pan mode fix), `e281cf3` (mousedown fix), `d917984` (getScreenCTM fix)\n\n## NEXT STEPS\n\n1. **Fix zoom in sheets mode** — Investigation started but interrupted. Found that `SheetsView` renders instead of `DiagramDisplay` when sheets are active. Need to read `SheetsView.tsx` and `SheetRenderer` to understand what's missing, then either:\n   - Add zoom/pan support to SheetsView/SheetRenderer\n   - Or make the toolbar zoom buttons work with SheetsView's rendering\n\n2. **After zoom fix**: Deploy and have user test\n\n3. **Open issues remaining**:\n   - #53 [Low] `useElementPlacement.ts` is 1085 lines — needs refactoring\n   - #57 [High] — was the icon disappearance bug, now resolved\n\n## TODO LIST\nID if loaded: none\n\n## FACTUAL RECORD\n\n### Files Modified and Read\n_(Most frequently and recently accessed first. Indented items show summaries for the last 5 modifications.)_\n* /home/alfonsodg/Devel/ccvass/oss-projects/mer...mponents/canvas/CanvasElementInteractions.tsx (10 modifications, 10 reads, showing summaries for last 5 modifications)\n  - Remove duplicate lastPosition in drag mode init\n  - Remove duplicate lastPosition in pan mode init\n  - Add lastPosition to pointer up reset\n  - Add 